msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: A collection of commentaries on Aristotle's works concerning natural philosophy, including physics, astronomy, meteorology, and the soul.

msItem.title: Ad quatuor libros: De mundo et coelo; duo De generatione; quatuor De meteoris Aristotelicos tractatus qui Mundus dicitur, f. 179v
Ad quatuor libros meteorologicos Aristotelis, f. 307r
Ad libros tres De anima et ea quae vulgo dicuntur Parva naturalia tractatus, f. 329r

supportDesc.extent: 438 leaves : 222 x 168 (149 x 93) mm. bound to 229 x 179 mm

collation.p: Paper, 438 + i; 1-6¹² 7¹⁰ 8-9¹² 10¹²(-8) 11¹² 12¹⁴ 13-25¹² 26⁶ 27¹² 28¹⁰ 29-32¹² 33¹⁴ 34-37¹²; [1-438]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto; quires signed in modern pencil, lower right recto on first page of each gathering (a-z, aa-pp).

layoutDesc.layout: Written in long lines with consistent borders throughout, many annotations in margins in same hand as text body.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script, with caption headings in a humanistic cursive.

binding.p: Contemporary leather with name "CL. DECHAMPHEV." on upper cover; older paper with fragments of a religious text in a Gothic script visible under pastedowns on upper and lower covers.

origin.p: Written in France in the 16th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Sold by Laurence Witten (New Haven, Conn.), 1962.
